csv2json
========

Convert CSVs to JSON with ease! Excitement! Rainbows!

csv2json will output either JSON objects (k=>v mappings), or just an array of 
parsed rows. Simply add the -h flag to your command to indicate that the first row of your CSV contains column names, and your json will be outputted as an array of objects with k=>v mappings.

For exmaple:

ruby csv2json.rb -h -r csv_with_headers.csv:output.json
ruby csv2json.rb -h -r csv_with_headers.csv:output1.json csv_with_headers2.csv:output2.json (make multiple conversions, all with headers)
ruby csv2json.rb -h -r /path/to/dir/of/csvs (convert an entire dir of CSVs -- all files will be outputted in /path/to/dir/of/csvs with .json extension)

ruby csv2json.rb csv_no_headers.csv:output.json (will output array of rows)

Use it wisely, soldier.